						               													<description>The Sightseeing board game presents Budapest to the preschool and primary school age group on four large boards. It is the smallest of the four games of different difficulty and theme, and those who can already read will find it age-appropriate. The game guides both Budapesters and non-Budapesters through the capital.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Br&amp;uacute;n&amp;oacute; in Budapest board game contains 4 different games that are related to the book series Br&amp;uacute;n&amp;oacute; in Budapest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules are simple and easy to follow in all 4 games and can be played in an average of 15-20 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Simplified, Erika Bartos's drawings introduce children to Budapest's famous buildings and public spaces in a perfectly recognizable way. The game is also suitable for children who like transport and means of transport.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cube-based vehicle game is easy even for the little ones: the winner is the first to collect the six vehicles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The second board is a classic party, where the winner will be the first to get from Vajdahunyad Castle to the Elizabeth Lookout Tower.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the third game, we have to go around the border of the capital, and the surrounding settlements and the building drawings on the map and the numbers and boundaries of the districts help to get to know our capital.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The fourth answer table builds on the knowledge of Budapest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is recommended for 3-10 year olds. It can be played by 2 to 8 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
